# Function to get array of pixels of an image

def get_pixels(image_path):
    image = Image.open(image_path)
    display(image)
    img_arr = asarray(image)
    pixels = img_arr.reshape((-1, 3))
    return pixels

def get_pixels_image(image_path):
    image = Image.open(image_path)
    display(image)
    img_arr = asarray(image)
    pixels = img_arr.reshape((-1, 3))
    return pixels, image

# Function to perform K-Means clustering

def kmeans_clustering(points, k):
    initial_mean_points = mean_points = randint(0, 256, (k, points.shape[1]))
    iteration_count = 0
    old_mean_points = None
    clusters = None
    while not (iteration_count>0 and  (mean_points==old_mean_points).all()):
        clusters = [[] for _ in range(len(mean_points))]
        for point in points:
            dis = ((mean_points - point)**2).sum(axis=1)
            chosen_cluster_index = dis.argmin()
            clusters[chosen_cluster_index].append(point)
        old_mean_points = mean_points
        mps = []
        for cluster in clusters:
            if len(cluster)==0:
                mps.append(old_mean_points[len(mps)-1])
                continue
            mean_point = asarray(cluster).mean(axis=0)
            mps.append(mean_point)
        mean_points = asarray(mps)
        iteration_count+=1
    return mean_points, clusters, iteration_count, initial_mean_points

# Function to display colors

def display_colors(colors):
    s=''
    for color in colors:
        s+=f'<div style="background-color:rgb({int(color[0])},{int(color[1])},{int(color[2])}); display:inline-block; margin:2px; border:2px solid #888; height:50px; width:50px;"></div>'
    display(HTML(s))

# Function to perform image segmentation

def image_segmentation(image, clusters, mean_points):
    img_arr = asarray(image).copy()
    for i, cluster in enumerate(clusters):
        clusters[i] = set(map(tuple, cluster))
    shape = img_arr.shape
    img_arr = img_arr.reshape(-1, 3)
    for i, p in enumerate(img_arr):
        p = tuple(p)
        for k, cluster in enumerate(clusters):
            if p in cluster:
                img_arr[i] = mean_points[k]
                break
    img_arr = img_arr.reshape(shape)
    return Image.fromarray(img_arr)

# Example 1

pixels, image = get_pixels_image('sample_data/triangle.jpeg')
results = kmeans_clustering(pixels, k = 4)
print('\nNo. of iterations:', results[2], end='\n\n')
display_colors(results[0])
segmented_image = image_segmentation(image, results[1], results[0])
display(segmented_image)

No. of iterations: 10
